    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - PRINCIPLES, OPERATION AND SERVICE - REMOVE - EXCITER RING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EXCITER RING</title>
        <para>To remove the exciter ring, first remove the brake drum from the wheel hub. Then remove the hub from the
            vehicle. Using a suitable puller,
            <emph type="bold">lightly heat</emph>
            the exciter ring to expand it and remove from wheel assembly.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
